text: The Papua wrinkled ground frog (Cornufer papuensis) is a frog. It lives in Papua New Guinea, Indonesia, and islands nearby. People have seen it between 0 and 1200 meters above sea level. The adult male frog can be as big as 46 mm long from nose to rear end and the adult female frog can be 64 mm long. The female frog lays eggs on land. The eggs hatch into young frogs. This frog is never a tadpole. ==References== Category:Frogs of Oceania
title: Cornufer papuensis
